                  <summary>The <title>Dabistān al-Maẕāhib</title> (School of Religions).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_189-item1">
                     <editor key="person_f1839" role="scr" >
                        <persName xml:lang="hi-Latn-x-lc" change="#role-assignment">Kāshī Nath</persName> <foreign>کاشی ناته</foreign>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">Dabistān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">Tabṣirat al-Maz̲āhib va Taẕkira al-Adyān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">دبستان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">تبصرت المذاهب و تذکرت الادیان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">Dabistān al-Maẕāhib</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt" key="work_1537" change="#ids-cleanup">Dabistān-i Maẕāhib</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"> ای نام تو سر دفتر اطفال دبستان * یاد ببالغ نظران شمع شبستان.</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"> نسخه دبستان مذاهب بخط بنده کاشی ناتهه (؟) قوم بر همن متوطن ملک پنجاب بلده سیالکوت تحریر پذیرفت پانزدهم شهر رمضان المبارک سنه ۱۲۱۰ هجری .</colophon>
                     <colophon>
                        Completed by <persName key="person_f1839" role="scr" change="#role-assignment">Kāshī Nath</persName>, a Brahmin from city of <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/1083799" key="place_1083799">Sialkot, Punjab</placeName> on the <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1796-03-24">15 Ramaz̤ān 1210 AH (24 Mar. 1796 CE)</date>.
                     </colophon>
                     <!-- CHECK whether Lewin or just Bland owned this<listBibl>
                        <bibl>In a MS. note in this copy, former owner <persName>Samuel Hawtayne Lewin</persName> cites Sir W. Ouseley (<title>Travels</title> vol. iii, p. 564) ascription of the work to Mubid Shah and speaks of Muhsin Fani as only the "poet quoted at the beginning". This copy begins with a memorandum at the margin of page 1: Muhsin Fani says محسن فانی گوید which may only refer to authorship of those verses, not the entire work. Rieu describes a copy of this work ascribed to Shaykh Muḥsin Fanī Kashmīrī (Rieu, BM 142a-b). Another copy of this work (in a collection in Tehran University, No. 4389, vol xiii, p 3352) is ascribed to Shaykh Muḥammad Muḥsin Fanī Kashmīrī or Mullā Mūbid Shāh: از شیخ محمد محسن فانی کشمیری یا ملا موبد شاه</bibl>
                        <bibl type="related-text">another copy of <idno>Persian MS 75</idno>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                      -->
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>This copy begins with a memorandum on the margins of folio:<lb/>محسن فانی گوید... </note>
                  </msItem>
