                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item>
                           <label>Bookplates</label> Bibilotheca Lindesiana, Bland MSS No. 410</item>
                        <item>
                           <label>Marginalia</label> A note penciled on the <locus>fly leaf</locus> suggests that it previously belonged to library of the Governor <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/19247044/" key="person_19247044" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">Jonathan Duncan, 1756-1811</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <label>Marginalia</label> Some explanatory notes in English by <persName key="person_f2018" role="ann" change="#role-assignment">Lewin</persName>, who seems to agree with <name ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/18419237">Sir William Ouseley, 1767-1842</name>'s <title>Travels in Arabia</title> (iii, 564) in ascribing the work to <persName key="person_f3087" role="att" change="#role-assignment">Mūbid Shāh</persName>. He speaks of <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/47114320" key="person_47114320" role="att" change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">Muḥsin Fānī, -1671 or 1672</persName> to whom the work was previously ascribed as only the "poet quoted at the beginning".</item>
                     </list>
                     
                  </additions>
