               <history>
                  <origin>
                     Completed by <persName key="person_f1839" role="scr" change="#role-assignment">Kāshī Nath</persName>, possibly in <origPlace cert="medium" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/1083799" key="place_1083799">Sialkot, Punjab</origPlace> <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1796-03-24">15 Ramaz̤ān 1210 AH (24 Mar. 1796 CE)</date><origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1795">15th Ramazan 1210 AH (1795 CE)</origDate>.
                  </origin>
                  <provenance><p>Probably obtained in the <placeName>Indian subcontinent</placeName> by the Governor of Bombay, <persName role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/19247044" key="person_19247044">Jonathan Duncan (1756–1811)</persName>, after whose death <placeName>London</placeName> firm of <persName role="auc" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/17541837" key="person_17541837">Samuel Sotheby (1771–1842)</persName> where <persName role="fmo ins" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/32750828" key="person_32750828">Sir Graves Champney Haughton (1788–1849)</persName> for £12.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Since the catalogue for the posthumous 1851 sale of Haughton's library in Paris omits this title, either he sold it beforehand, or his family thereafter, likely to scholar <persName
                        type="standard" role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/"
                        key="person_20108923">Nathaniel Bland (1803–1865)</persName>, who lived in Paris for extended periods where he acquired many manuscripts.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>After Bland's
                     death, <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011781" key="place_7011781">London</placeName> bookseller <persName type="standard"
                           role="bsl" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/5679225/" key="person_5679225"
                           >Bernard Quaritch (1819–1899)</persName> sold his oriental manuscripts in
                        <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1866">1866</date> to <persName
                           type="standard" role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/"
                           key="person_97751058">Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford
                           (1812–1880)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Purchased by <persName type="standard" key="person_f6379"
                     role="dnr">Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date
                        calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from <persName
                           type="standard" role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/"
                           key="person_9985420">James Ludovic Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford
                           (1847–1913)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Bequeathed by <persName type="standard" key="person_f6379" role="dnr"
                        >Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian"
                           when="1908">1908</date> to the <orgName
                              ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/" role="rps">John Rylands
                              Library</orgName>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
